HEADWORD: Chelicera
<hw>Che*lic"e*ra</hw> <pr>(k⟦esl⟧*l⟦icr⟧s"⟦esl⟧*r⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Chelicer⟦ae⟧</plw>
<pr>(-r⟦emac⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>chhlh`</grk> claw +
<grk>ke`ras</grk> horn.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the
anterior pair of mouth organs, terminated by a pincherlike claw, in
scorpions and allied Arachnida. They are homologous with the falcers of
spiders, and probably with the mandibles of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>chelicerous</ent>⟦br⟧
